				<name type="primary" sortindex="5" value="The Golden Pyramid" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Golden Pyramid is a card driven game, where the players use colored cubes and tiles to collectively build a three-dimentional pyramid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The unchilded emperor needs a worthy successor to his throne. He declares that the nobles shall together build a golden pyramid. The emperor demands a pyramid that consists of four levels, with the upper levels being build upon colorful artistic colonnades. The one whose contribution impresses the emperor the most will become the new emperor.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to build a pyramid:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cubes in this game represent the columns of the pyramid and are bought by playing a card. The number or cubes a player may draw from the bag is determined by the value shown on the card. Cubes can also be obtained from a common market or by trading with other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To actually build a part of the pyramid the players need four cubes (second level or higher) and a card that shows the symbol of an available tile as well as a value that equals at least the level that should be build.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players mainly gain victory points by building tiles and placing cubes adjacent to already placed cubes of the same color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Golden Pyramid was one of two Gold Winners of the 2019 Contest X for the Green Box of Games. In order to play the game the Meeple Mini Expansion or replacements (20 white 10mm cubes, 20 black 10mm cubes, a drawbag and e.g. meeples in player colors) are needed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
